How are you disposed this morning? Will you walk down to Evans’s?<note>Messrs Evans, 93 Pall Mall, auctioneers.</note> I want to leave word about the books I have bought of poor Tom Hill’s,<note>Thomas Hill (1760-1840; <hi rend="italic">Dictionary of National Biography</hi>), retired dry-salter and book collector: see Pilgrim <hi rend="italic">Letters</hi> 1, p. 329n. CD invited him to the <hi rend="italic">Pickwick</hi> dinner (18 Nov 37) and gave him presentation copies. His books and manuscripts auctioned 10-17 Mar 40; CD attended the first day and sent someone to bid for him on the second. The marked catalogue (British Library) shows his numerous purchases: see Pilgrim <hi rend="italic">Letters</hi> 2, p. 229, <hi rend="italic">nn</hi> 2 &amp; 4 and p. 238.</note> and shall be glad of your company if you will go. A word in answer.  
